The paper proposes a multi-task recurrent neural network architecture for natural language tasks, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of auxiliary tasks and the gating and merging of state sequences are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG), and the paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms (cs.AI). The use of recurrent neural networks is also a common technique in natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed architecture to sentiment classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing.
